		<div id="comment_body_72359"><p>I really like this. I liked it even more as I worked through all of the examples to better understand them.  One thing I would change:</p><blockquote><div><p> <tt>say $_.perl for @pascal;</tt><span class="substr"> </span> </p></div></blockquote><p>The output is much clearer that way (at least to me).  I actually tried to get it a touch more "triangly":</p><blockquote><div><p> <tt>my @pascal<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:= do [1], -&gt; @p { [0,@p Z+ @p,0] }<nobr> <wbr></nobr>... *;<br>say ' ' x 2 * (10 - $_.elems), $_.perl for @pascal[^10];</tt> </p></div></blockquote><p>But wound up with this:</p><blockquote><div><p> <tt>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; [1]<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</tt></p></div></blockquote></div>
		
	
